Here is one or two examples, as a back-up solution, in case you can't download it from the cluster.

But, the best would be to download the whole directory on your own computer (yes, the space and the dot at the end of the command is important).
<code>scp -i c[XX].pem -r user[XX]@[WednesdayIPaddress]:"~/Day3_demography/data-honeybees/ABC-based_DILS/" .</code>

e.g. assuming that your are user2 and than you want to download the file in the same folder than where you have your pem file to login in:
<code>scp -i c2.pem -r user2@[WednesdayIPaddress]:"~/Day3_demography/data-honeybees/ABC-based_DILS/" .</code>
